                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15405738" author="paulk" created="Wed, 3 Aug 2016 11:12:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just to clarify, the remaining DGM methods on Iterator which call toList are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Iterator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; unique(Iterator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; self)
Iterator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; unique(Iterator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; self, @ClosureParams(value=FromString.class, options={&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;T&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;T,T&quot;&lt;/span&gt;}) Closure closure)
Iterator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; unique(Iterator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; self, Comparator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; comparator)

Iterator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; sort(Iterator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; self)
Iterator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; sort(Iterator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; self, Comparator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; comparator)
Iterator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; sort(Iterator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; self, @ClosureParams(value=FromString.class, options={&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;T&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;T,T&quot;&lt;/span&gt;}) Closure closure)

Iterator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; toSorted(Iterator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; self, Comparator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; comparator)

Iterator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; dropRight(Iterator&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; self, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; num)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Of these, &lt;tt&gt;sort&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;toSorted&lt;/tt&gt; aren&apos;t likely to gain us much. The &lt;tt&gt;dropRight&lt;/tt&gt; method will have only minor gains. The &lt;tt&gt;unique&lt;/tt&gt; methods should be relatively easy though we already have Iterator specific &lt;tt&gt;toUnique&lt;/tt&gt; methods.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15405824" author="paulk" created="Wed, 3 Aug 2016 12:15:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;dropRight&lt;/tt&gt; method now has an iterator-backed implementation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15407162" author="paulk" created="Thu, 4 Aug 2016 05:00:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;unique&lt;/tt&gt; closure variant now calls through to the comparator version, so one more off the list.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15407202" author="paulk" created="Thu, 4 Aug 2016 05:40:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I removed some superfluous calls to &lt;tt&gt;toList&lt;/tt&gt; from the &lt;tt&gt;unique&lt;/tt&gt; methods. Since for &lt;tt&gt;unique&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;sort&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;toSorted&lt;/tt&gt; we have to traverse the Iterator entirely anyway, I don&apos;t think providing additional iterator-backed implementations will gain us much, so I am going to close this issue now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
